2. A single farm config like this one is great for a demo environment or for training purposes (I didn&#039;t really implement a secure environment here). It could also be used as a development environment. However, it is not secure and not scalable at all.&lt;br /&gt;
If you want a reliable scalable environment, you need to go with the multi farm config. I&#039;m no SharePoint expert, so I didn&#039;t go with this set-up in the blog series. It wasn&#039;t needed anyway, because I just wanted it to run on my laptop.

